title: To Hon To
text:
To Hon To (, born 4 April 1989) is a former <a href="Hong%20Kong%20people">Hong Kong</a> professional <a href="Association%20football">football</a> player who is currently playing as an amateur player for <a href="Hong%20Kong%20First%20Division%20League">Hong Kong First Division</a> club <a href="Eastern%20District%20SA">Eastern District</a>. His position is <a href="Forward%20%28association%20football%29">forward</a>.
Club career.
To is the top scorer of the reserve league in the 2007–2008 season which he scored 18 goals in 21 games.
International career.
To was a member of the <a href="Hong%20Kong%20national%20under-23%20football%20team">Hong Kong national under-23 football team</a> for the 2012 London Olympics qualifiers. He scored two goals against Maldives on 23 February 2011 to help Hong Kong secure a 4:0 victory.
